 "executive_summary": "This study determined the crystal structure of the immunodominant anti-influenza V(\u03b2)17V(\u03b1)10.2 TCR bound to the MP(58-66) peptide presented by HLA-A2, at 1.4 \u00c5 resolution. The structure reveals an unusual binding geometry in which the TCR sits nearly orthogonal to the peptide-MHC groove, allowing a conserved arginine from the V(\u03b2) CDR3 to insert into a surface notch formed by MP(58-66) itself rather than contacting exposed peptide side chains\u2014a previously undescribed interaction mode. This distinctive binding mechanism explains why V(\u03b2)17V(\u03b1)10.2 TCRs dominate the CD8+ T cell response to influenza matrix protein in HLA-A2-positive individuals, providing a molecular basis for immunodominant TCR selection in natural infection.",
